/Stamford_Transportation_Center\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stamford_Transportation_Center\"}, {\"begin\": 376, \"end\": 382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999994914102374, \"rank\": 5.085898586694328e-07, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 399, \"end\": 408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.985484424070572, \"rank\": 0.014729381383079275, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 414, \"end\": 426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.8906638065270787e-13, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This will only be the second-ever Olympic surfing competition after the sport debuted during the Summer Games in Tokyo in 2021 and will take place nearly 10,000 miles away from the center of Olympic action in Paris.\", \"from\": 495, \"to\": 710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 608, \"end\": 613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999862756249532, \"rank\": 1.3700867213850099e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 704, \"end\": 709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.642344832438685e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jost will travel to Tahiti in advance of the competition, which begins on July 27, where he will preview the waves and interview athletes.\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 850, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 732, \"end\": 738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999994914102374, \"rank\": 5.085898586694328e-07, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Colin Jost hit the NBC Sports jackpot with an epic assignment covering surfing in Tahiti for the Paris Olympics,\\\" saysMolly Solomon, Executive Producer and President, Production, NBC Olympics.\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 1045, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 853, \"end\": 863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colin_Jost\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Colin Jost\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colin_Jost\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colin_Jost\"}, {\"begin\": 872, \"end\": 882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999996057755065, \"rank\": 2.139390255771813e-07, \"text\": \"NBC Sports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 935, \"end\": 941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999994914102374, \"rank\": 5.085898586694328e-07, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 986, \"end\": 1004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Executive_producer\", \"score\": 0.9978391923304272, \"rank\": 0.002165486319493267, \"text\": \"Executive Producer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Executive_producer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Executive_producer\"}, {\"begin\": 1032, \"end\": 1044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Although the setting is a little different than theWeekend Updatedesk in Studio 8H, Colin, an avid surfer, is going to bring his unique flair to reporting on the competition, athletes, and beautiful surroundings in one of the most breathtaking Olympic venues ever.\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1311, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1120, \"end\": 1129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Studio_8H\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.917364720868896e-28, \"text\": \"Studio 8H\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Studio_8H\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Studio_8H\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tune in to see if he catches a wave for America.\\\"\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1361, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am honored to get to watch the best surfers in the world compete on one of the heaviest waves imaginable, and to help showcase the rich history of surfing in Tahiti,\\\" said Jost.\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1524, \"end\": 1530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999994914102374, \"rank\": 5.085898586694328e-07, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 1538, \"end\": 1542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Jost\", \"score\": 0.9999545890657053, \"rank\": 4.5412965994389404e-05, \"text\": \"Jost\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Jost\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Jost\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And my Writer's Guild Health Insurance is excited to see what the coral reef does to my back.\\\"\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1639, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jost's role will complement NBCU's traditional surfing coverage that will featureJoe Turpelhandling play-by-play andMichael Parsonsas analyst.\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1783, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1641, \"end\": 1645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Jost\", \"score\": 0.9999545890657053, \"rank\": 4.5412965994389404e-05, \"text\": \"Jost\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Jost\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Jost\"}, {\"begin\": 1669, \"end\": 1673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCU\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympic surfing competition will take place over four days within a 10-day window from July 27-August 5 due to possible weather delays which are common for the sport.\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 1961, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1789, \"end\": 1794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.642344832438685e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition will feature both a men's and women's shortboard event, with 24 surfers from each gender competing for the three coveted Olympic podium spots.\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 2120, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States'Carissa Moore, the reigning Olympic gold medalist and five-time World Surf League Women's World Tour Champion, aims to defend her Olympic title.\", \"from\": 2121, \"to\": 2283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2147, \"end\": 2152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Moore\", \"score\": 0.9998557044561305, \"rank\": 0.00010883691630389001, \"text\": \"Moore\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Moore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Moore\"}, {\"begin\": 2203, \"end\": 2220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.621455853932091e-18, \"text\": \"World Surf League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tahiti is a legendary surfing location and has become a world-renowned spot for surfers due to its breathtaking waves and beaches.\", \"from\": 2285, \"to\": 2415, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2285, \"end\": 2291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999994914102374, \"rank\": 5.085898586694328e-07, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For over two decades, Teahupo'o has hosted the Pro Tahiti world championship event, establishing itself as a stalwart of the men's championship tour, and where icons of the sport such asKelly Slater,Gabriel Medina, andMark Occhilupohave competed.\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jost has been co-anchor ofSNL'sWeekend Updatesince 2014 and has been a writer on the show since 2005, serving as a head writer for a combined eight years (2012-2015, 2017-2022).\", \"from\": 2664, \"to\": 2841, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jost has been nominated for 14 Emmy Awards and has won multiple Writers Guild of America Awards, as well as two Peabody Awards.\", \"from\": 2842, \"to\": 2969, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2873, \"end\": 2884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmy_Awards\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0088318958177529e-15, \"text\": \"Emmy Awards\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmy_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmy_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"***  In Paris this summer, the world's greatest athletes will compete against the backdrop of one of the most beautiful cities in the world where the modern Olympic Games were conceived 130 years ago.\", \"from\": 2971, \"to\": 3171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2979, \"end\": 2984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.642344832438685e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This will be the third time Paris has hosted the Olympics (1900 and 1924), tying London for the most as a Summer Games host.\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3296, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3200, \"end\": 3205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.642344832438685e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3253, \"end\": 3259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999949839892289, \"rank\": 4.996749797862468e-06, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Los Angeles (1932, 1984) will tie those two cities when it hosts the first Summer Games in the U.S. in 32 years in 2028.\", \"from\": 3297, \"to\": 3417, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3297, \"end\": 3308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999590727, \"rank\": 4.110887652250765e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The organizers of Paris 2024 are reimagining the Games to make them more accessible to the public and to showcase their city to the world.\", \"from\": 3419, \"to\": 3557, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a first, competitions will be held amidst iconic Parisian landmarks - beach volleyball at the Eiffel Tower, equestrian at the Palace of Versailles and urban sports at Place de la Concorde.\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3728, \"end\": 3748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.541946391438825e-15, \"text\": \"Place de la Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The NBC broadcast network and streaming service Peacock will be the company's primary platforms for its coverage of the Olympic Games Paris 2024, scheduled for July 26-Aug. 11, 2024.\", \"from\": 3751, \"to\": 3933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3755, \"end\": 3758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9869640414560477, \"rank\": 0.010117924489571158, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Clickherefor more linear programming information andherefor more about the Olympic experience on Peacock.\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 4039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4031, \"end\": 4038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999999999872671, \"rank\": 1.2893657428273112e-11, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBCU owns the U.S. media rights to the Olympic Games through 2032, which are scheduled for Paris (2024), Milan Cortina (2026), Los Angeles (2028) and Brisbane (2032).\", \"from\": 4041, \"to\": 4207, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4041, \"end\": 4045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCU\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 4132, \"end\": 4137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.642344832438685e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4146, \"end\": 4151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"score\": 0.9999165483839598, \"rank\": 8.345857891258135e-05, \"text\": \"Milan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\"}, {\"begin\": 4152, \"end\": 4159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.704533318958453e-22, \"text\": \"Cortina\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\"}, {\"begin\": 4168, \"end\": 4179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999590727, \"rank\": 4.110887652250765e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 4191, \"end\": 4199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"score\": 0.9999999837573342, \"rank\": 1.1167649025631955e-08, \"text\": \"Brisbane\", \"types\": [\"Q515